<h2>Spring 2012 Semiannual Report</h2>

<a target="_blank" style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% transparent; padding: 0pt;" href="/reports-and-publications/archives/semiannual/2012/spring/sar-S12-fulltext.pdf"><img src="/reports-and-publications/archives/semiannual/2012/spring/2012spring.png" class="r" alt="Cover of the Spring 2012 Semiannual Report"></a>



<p>The Office of Inspector General's (OIG) Semiannual Report to Congress keeps the Secretary of the Department of Health &amp; Human Services and Congress currently informed about OIG's most significant findings, recommendations, and activities for specific 6-month periods.  Historically, about 80 percent of OIG's resources are directed to work related to Medicare and Medicaid.  This is mirrored in the organization and content of the report.</p>

<p>This spring edition of the Semiannual Report to Congress covers October 1, 2011 to March 31, 2012.  In addition to the full-text version, we provide below smaller breakout files of the major parts of the document.</p>

